<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-10-17T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-10-17T12:00:00-05:00" n="541" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d541">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">511.4R1/55: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Siam</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Kaufman</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-10-17T12:00:00-05:00">October 17,
                                1931—noon</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>27. Please inform Foreign Office that Colonel Lucien R. Sweet of the
                            Philippine Constabulary is being sent to Bangkok to assist Caldwell at
                            Conference on Opium Smoking.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>